            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="0"/>
                <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/> <lb n="1"/>Corona quern<supplied reason="lost">ea uti super ianuam domus <expan><abbr>Imp</abbr><ex>eratoris</ex></expan> Caesaris</supplied> <lb n="2"/>Augusti poner<supplied reason="lost">etur senatus decrevit quod rem <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>ublicam</ex></expan></supplied> <lb n="3"/><expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>opulo</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>R</abbr><ex>omano</ex></expan> rest<supplied reason="lost">i</supplied>tui<supplied reason="lost">t</supplied>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Fasti. (B): Rekonstruktionsvorschlag des Autors orientiert sich an Mommsens Ergänzung und modifiziert diese, charakterisiert als &amp;quot;&amp;quot;less improbable than the other&amp;quot;&amp;quot; (Judge 298): corona querc[ea autem id est civica uti super ianuam] / Augusti poner[etur quod civibus ab eo servatis ipse] / p.R. rest[it]u[i sibi videbatur eodem s.c. sanctum est].</p>
            </div>
